The paper deals with the art gallery problem, which is a classical problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity status of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of polynomial equations and real algebraic numbers also suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
